<dependency>
  <groupId>org.modelmapper</groupId>
  <artifactId>modelmapper</artifactId>
  <version>3.2.4</version>
</dependency>

----------------------------------  this is for mapping entity to dto . Instead of wrtiting the same conversion of object yoe again and again.
it specifies we are creating different types of beans.


@Configuration
public class MapperConfig {

    @Bean
    public ModelMapper modelMapper(){
        return new ModelMapper();
    }
}   ------------------- here we are just making a bean using configuration to specify wt it must do.


private final ModelMapper modelMapper;


studentEntity student = studentRepository.findById(id).orElseThrow(() -> new IllegalArgumentException("Student not found with id" + id));
studentDto studentDto = modelMapper.map(student, studentDto.class);


student has - studentEntity object. but we must convert it into studentDto.

Method 1 - new studentDto(student.getId(),student.getName(),student.getAge()) --- but this will be done for every method u do .

Method 2 - studentDto studentDto = modelMapper.map(student, studentDto.class);

where student - studentEntity object
to studentDto.class object.
